<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2183200-sequoyah">Sequoyah</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It’s a novel written in the fifties about people from the south in the same time period. Yes, it is a reflection of the southern zeitgeist at that tim<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It’s a novel written in the fifties about people from the south in the same time period. Yes, it is a reflection of the southern zeitgeist at that time, at least in the vernacular. You should separate the art from the author. The main character is a man, yet the author wasn’t, so I don’t see why a truthful depiction of 1950’s south should be a reflection of the author’s own beliefs. Rather, it is simply just a story with racist characters.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
